WEBVTT

00:12.151 --> 00:13.601
<i>Hey, uh, you guys remember Fantasy Island?</i>

00:13.653 --> 00:16.604
You know, tattoo, Mr. Roarke,
"the plane! The plane!"

00:16.656 --> 00:19.106
- Oh, you do that well!
- Yeah, "the plane, the plane!"

00:19.158 --> 00:20.441
He obviously does it all day then,

00:20.493 --> 00:22.943
'cause that was his regular voice.

00:22.996 --> 00:25.079
Let's say you were able
to go to fantasy island.

00:25.114 --> 00:26.947
What fantasy would you live out?

00:27.000 --> 00:28.499
Good question.

00:28.534 --> 00:30.201
If I were to go, I think
I'd like to see, uh,

00:30.203 --> 00:31.786
what it'd be like to be
like, massively wealthy.

00:31.838 --> 00:34.088
Don't you realize it
only lasted for a weekend?

00:34.123 --> 00:36.674
So you get that taste and then you're like,

00:36.709 --> 00:38.042
♪ wha wha ♪

00:38.044 --> 00:39.210
What about you Mike?

00:39.212 --> 00:40.795
Uh, I was always curious about, you know,

00:40.847 --> 00:43.381
ancient Roman times and... you know...

00:43.433 --> 00:47.718
I would live out the
last weekend of Pompeii.

00:47.770 --> 00:49.720
Is that... are you talking
about, like, the volcano?

00:49.772 --> 00:51.055
Yeah.

00:51.057 --> 00:52.056
48 hours of sheer terror.

00:52.058 --> 00:55.443
[Laughter]

00:55.478 --> 00:57.895
I think my fantasy would be:

00:57.947 --> 01:00.031
Work at the stash, but I get mondays off.

01:00.066 --> 01:01.899
That sounds more like unfantasy island

01:01.901 --> 01:03.284
<i>than Fantasy Island.</i>

01:03.319 --> 01:04.617
So wait a second, isn't
it only for the weekend?

01:04.654 --> 01:05.953
So you wouldn't even
experience that Monday.

01:05.988 --> 01:08.072
[Laughter]

01:08.074 --> 01:11.242
It's like, [Bleep] That's
right, I gotta work tomorrow.

01:11.244 --> 01:13.294
[Heroic music]

01:13.329 --> 01:15.963
[Laughs]

01:15.998 --> 01:17.465
♪ ♪

01:17.500 --> 01:20.167
[Roaring]

01:20.219 --> 01:29.260
